Generally, dragons can expect to live to 1,200 years in good health, and many live a great deal longer. Very rarely, the most ancient of dragons can achieve a form of apotheosis, transforming into [[greatwyrm]]s. 

!!! Regional Effects

The innate magic of an old and powerful dragon can warp the region surrounding its lair, creating magical anomalies as far as six miles away. These effects are automatic, and the dragon cannot easily suppress them. Regional effects tend to be more hostile for chromatic dragons ([[black|black dragon]], [[blue|blue dragon]], [[green|green dragon]], [[red|red dragon]], and [[white|white dragon]]); for example, the presence of a mighty [[black dragon]] fouls nearby water sources, while a [[blue dragon]] generates fierce thunderstorms wherever it settles. By contrast, metallic dragons ([[brass|brass dragon]], [[bronze|bronze dragon]], [[copper|copper dragon]], [[gold|gold dragon]], and [[silver|silver dragon]]) generate effects that are seen as more benign or even pleasant. This fact has led some, including the controversial [[loredrake]] [[Ourenilach]], to advance the idea that chromatic dragons are touched by [[Khyber]], while metallic dragons are more aligned with [[Siberys]]. This fact is also a reason the [[Chamber]] uses younger dragons as its undercover operatives.

!! Origin of the Dragons

According to the draconic faith known as [[Thir]], the birth of the first dragons predates even the rising of the [[overlord]]s. In the wake of the battle of the [[Progenitors|Progenitor Dragons]], life emerged on the new world. [[Siberys]] had fallen in battle, but power
remained within his blood. Filled with the purest essence of magic, that blood fell on [[Eberron]], merging life and magic to produce new creatures with the strength of both Progenitors. Where the blood of Siberys struck the clouds, [[silver dragon]]s were born. It fell on the cold peaks, and [[white dragon]]s rose from the ice. It struck the swamps, and [[black dragon]]s emerged from the dark depths. And so all the dragons were born, mighty and proud, possessing the mystical power of Siberys and the vibrant life force of Eberron.

Few of the creatures of the modern age existed at the dawn of time. The [[titan|giant]]s of [[Xen'drik]] were in their infancy, possessed of power but lacking knowledge. The lesser races had not been born; the dark creatures had not been spawned. So it was that wild flights of dragons soared above the world, reveling in their might.

For untold millennia, the dragons were the sole lords of Eberron. Then a new threat emerged. [[Khyber]] was bound in the depths of Eberron, but this did not eliminate the dark dragon’s power. In time, a host of horrors spawned in the depths. The mighty [[overlord]]s, served by [[rakshasa]]s, [[aboleth]]s, and other terrors, emerged to lay claim to the world above. The [[Age of Demons]] had begun.

!! Psionics and Dragons

For the dragons of [[Eberron]], the path of [[psionics]] is a dangerous one. An innate connection to [[arcane magic]] flows in a dragon's blood, and for reasons not fully understood, psionic power often twists and debases this force. Among those dragons who explore the psionic mysteries, the fortunate suffer only disfigurement and ill health. Many develop debilitating insanity, then ultimately die. It's possible that the vicious [[Sarlona]]n [[aberration]]s known as [[essence reaver]]s are the result of failed attempts by ancient [[dragon]]s to command the power of [[psionics]].

By contrast, the mysterious [[gem dragon]]s possess a powerful and innate psionic power. These creatures are not of this reality, and originate from the same previous incarnation of Eberron as the [[gith]].

!! Draconic Creatures

Some creatures share a common ancestry with true dragons, or perhaps are [[fey]] reflections of dragons, but are not true dragons themselves. These include [[wyvern]]s, [[kobold]]s, [[dragonborn]], [[dragon turtle]]s, and [[pseudodragon]]s.

